DaVinci simulation and visualization

Setup

This document demonstrates a complete DaVinci analysis workflow using simulated spatial transcriptomics data. We begin by loading required packages and setting the working directory.

library(DaVinci)
library(anndata)
library(ggpubr)

setwd("~/For_Tutorial/Simulation/")

Load the data

We load the AnnData (.h5ad) object, which stores gene expression counts, spatial coordinates, and ground-truth spatial factors. The data was available at https://github.com/willtownes/nsf-paper/tree/main/simulations/bm_sp/data/.

dat <- read_h5ad("/mnt/home/wmao1/For_Tutorial/Simulation/data/S1.h5ad")

Prepare input matrices

The gene expression matrix is extracted from the counts layer and transposed so that rows correspond to genes and columns correspond to spatial spots. Spatial coordinates are taken from obsm$spatial.

gene.exp <- t(dat$layers['counts'])
rownames(gene.exp) <- paste0("feature_", 1:nrow(gene.exp))
colnames(gene.exp) <- paste0("spot_", 1:ncol(gene.exp))

coor <- dat$obsm$spatial
colnames(coor) <- c("array_row", "array_col")
rownames(coor) <- colnames(gene.exp)

Visualize ground truth spatial factors

The ground-truth spatial factors stored in obsm$spfac are visualized to provide a reference for evaluating the DaVinci results.

gt <- dat$obsm$spfac

plot.list <- list()
for (ii in seq_len(ncol(gt))) {
  plot.list[[ii]] <- scatter.DiscretePlot(
    coor = coor,
    cluster.label = gt[, ii],
    pt.size = 1,
    orientation = "x-y"
  ) +
    ggtitle(paste0("Ground Truth ", ii)) +
    theme(
      plot.title = element_text(size = 20, hjust = 0.5),
      legend.position = "none"
    ) +
    coord_fixed(ratio = 1)
}

ggarrange(plotlist = plot.list, nrow = 1)

Preprocessing and DaVinci decomposition

We preprocess the gene expression data to construct a spatial graph (delaunay triangulation) and then run DaVincis spatially-aware decomposition for multiple values of the regularization parameter L3.

fin <- preprocess(
  gene.exp,
  coor,
  type = "rna",
  graph.opt = "Tri.mesh",
  frac.thr = 0.95
)
## rna normalization finishes.
## Graph generation finishes.
L3.arg.opts <- c(0, 100, 1600, 6400, 12800, 25600, 33600)
res.list <- list()

for (ii in seq_along(L3.arg.opts)) {
  message("Running L3 = ", L3.arg.opts[ii])
  res.list[[ii]] <- manifoldDecomp(
    fin$mat,
    fin$L,
    k = 4,
    L4 = L3.arg.opts[ii],
    verbose = F
  )
}

Visualization of DaVinci results

For each value of L3, we visualize the latent variables learned by DaVinci.

to_plot <- list()

for (jj in seq_along(L3.arg.opts)) {
  ICAp.res <- res.list[[jj]]
  plot.list <- list()

  for (ii in seq_len(nrow(ICAp.res$B))) {
    plot.list[[ii]] <- scatter.FeaturePlot(
      coor = coor,
      LVs = ICAp.res$B[ii, ],
      plot.all = T,
      pt.size = 1,
      orientation = "x-y",
      ratio = 1,
      percentile = c(0.05, 0.95)
    ) +
      labs(color = rownames(ICAp.res$B)[ii]) +
      theme(legend.title = element_text(size = 15))
  }

  to_plot[[jj]] <- ggarrange(plotlist = plot.list, ncol = 1) +
    ggtitle(bquote(~ lambda[3] == .(L3.arg.opts[jj]))) +
    theme(
      plot.title = element_text(size = 30, hjust = 0.1),
      legend.position = "none"
    )
}
